# Monolith MCP — Project Instructions

This project uses **Monolith** for Unreal Engine MCP integration. 18 tools, 1,125 actions across 15 domains.

## Tools

- `monolith_discover(namespace?)` — List available actions (always call this first)
- `monolith_status()` — Health check, version, action count
- `monolith_reindex()` — Trigger full project re-index
- `blueprint_query(action, params)` — Blueprint CRUD, compile, nodes, spawn actors (88 actions)
- `material_query(action, params)` — Materials, instances, functions, HLSL, graph (57 actions)
- `animation_query(action, params)` — Animation assets, ABP, PoseSearch, montages (115 actions)
- `niagara_query(action, params)` — Niagara VFX, dynamic inputs, sim stages (96 actions)
- `mesh_query(action, params)` — Mesh inspection, scene manipulation, spatial queries, blockout, GeometryScript, procedural geometry (242 actions)
- `editor_query(action, params)` — Build, logs, compile output, crash context, scene capture (19 actions)
- `config_query(action, params)` — Config/INI resolution (6 actions)
- `source_query(action, params)` — Engine C++ source lookup, class hierarchy, callers/callees (11 actions)
- `project_query(action, params)` — Project-wide asset search (7 actions)
- `ui_query(action, params)` — Widget blueprints, templates, styling, accessibility (42 actions)
- `gas_query(action, params)` — Gameplay Ability System: abilities, attributes, effects, ASC (130 actions)
- `ai_query(action, params)` — AI: Behavior Trees, State Trees, EQS, Smart Objects, Perception, Navigation (229 actions)
- `combograph_query(action, params)` — ComboGraph combo systems (13 actions, requires ComboGraph plugin)
- `logicdriver_query(action, params)` — Logic Driver Pro state machines (66 actions, requires Logic Driver Pro plugin)

## Workflow

1. Call `monolith_discover("namespace")` to see actions before guessing names
2. Use `project_query("search", {"query": "..."})` to find assets
3. Use `source_query("search_source", {"query": "..."})` to look up UE C++ APIs
4. Use domain tools to inspect/modify assets
5. After C++ changes: `editor_query("get_build_errors")` to check results

## Asset Paths

All paths use `/Game/Path/To/Asset` format (no `.uasset`):
- Project Content: `/Game/Path/To/Asset`
- Project Plugins: `/PluginName/PluginName/Path/To/Asset`
- Engine plugins: `/PluginName/Path/To/Asset`

## Rules

- Always discover before calling — action names change between versions
- Never guess `#include` paths or UE API signatures — use `source_query` to verify
- The project index is pre-built — use `project_query` for broad searches
- For material work: `create_material` → `build_material_graph` → `connect_expressions` → `recompile_material`
